author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Jefferson blanks Morgan County in 8-AAA victory
text:
Saturday October 10th, 2015 4:20AM Posted 8:30AM on Saturday 10th October 2015 ( 4 hours from now ) Jefferson blanks Morgan County in 8-AAA victory By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 7: Region title, playoff races take shape after big night VIDEO: Brown, Lanier defense spark Longhorns to tough win over GHS 
JEFFERSON -- The Jefferson defense held Morgan County to just 136 total yards and pitched its second shutout of the season Friday night in a 17-0 win at Memorial Stadium. 
Colby Wood outgained the entire Bulldogs offense rushing for 153 yards and scored twice to lead the Dragons (7-0, 3-0 Region 8-AA) to a key region win. 
Wood scored on a 1-yard run in the first quarter and added a 2-yard scoring run in the second quarter. Freshman Hayden Kilgore booted a 34-yard field goal in the second quarter to give Jefferson a 17-0 halftime lead. 
The Dragons then clamped down on the Bulldogs (3-3, 1-1). 
Morgan County will play host to Oconee County next week while Jefferson will travel to East Jackson in 8-AAA contests. Associated Categories : Friday Game Night, High School Sports , Sports Associated Tags : High school football, Jefferson football Â© Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
